          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Mass resolving power A/delta-A = 400. The mass",
                " and charge yields were measured at only a few ionic",
                " charge states carefully chosen at selected fragment",
                " kinetic energies. Yields at other states and energies",
                " determined by interpolation or extrapolation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Filled with pure CH4 gas at 140 milli-bar. The",
                " chamber is positioned so that each of the three",
                " entrance windows (12 x 1.8 cm2) lie in the focal plane",
                " of the mass separator. The windows are made of",
                " stretched polypropylene foils of 50 micro-g/cm2",
                " supported by a grid of 90% transparency. Measured",
                " resolution was 800 keV at 100 MeV fragment energy.",
                " Nuclear charge measurements performed by measuring",
                " the residual energy behind a homogeneous absorber of",
                " 10 thin Parylene C-foils of total thickness",
                " 900 micro-g/cm2 which reduced initial fragment energy",
                " by 70%. The foils are mounted on a 7 x 1 cm2 holder in",
                " front of the central window of the chamber. Nuclear",
                " charge resolving power Z/delta-Z = 50, though charges",
                " higher than Z = 48 cannot be resolved, hence study",
                " restricted to yields of light fragment group."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Layer of 237-Np oxide (NpO2) thickness 100 micro-g/cm2",
                " deposited on a thick titanium backing and covered with",
                " a tantalum layer also of 100 micro-g/cm2. The fissile",
                " nuclide 238-Np is produced in situ by 237-Np + n, and",
                " the maximum fission activity resulting from the 239-Np",
                " fission channel occurs 5 days after installing the new",
                " target (activity 4.0E+9 fissions/sec for 100 micro-g",
                " of 237-Np). The competing beta decay channel of 238-Np",
                " (t1/2 = 2.117 days) results in parasitic fission",
                " activity from 238-Pu + n and 239-Pu + n, and to keep",
                " the activity from these Pu channels below 5% of the",
                " 239-Np fission activity the 237-Np target had to be",
                " changed every week; in total 10 fresh target were used",
                " in the experiment."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Changes in target properties owing to high flux and",
                " fission activity are accounted for by two empirical",
                " corrections as a function of time determined by",
                " observation of prominent A/q lines. These changes",
                " result from the loss of material produced by recoiling",
                " fission fragments and the diffusion of the 237-Np",
                " atoms through the Ta layer and Ti backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
